cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.NE 

This paper deals with image processing techniques for enhancing visual quality of images in bad weather conditions. The proposed approach involves simultaneous defogging and demosaicking, which are both sub-fields of computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The paper also mentions the suppression of noise amplification, which is a signal processing problem (cs.MM) and the use of theoretical analysis, which could fall under information theory (cs.IT) or neural networks (cs.NE).
